        <td bgcolor='dimgray' valign=top width='100' nowrap><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'><b>Smaaug</b></font></td>
        <td bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>I was going to post this to a petition site but they seem to be having problems.  I will try again tonight but til then.</P><P><a href="http://darqsmoke.8m.net/Necromancers.htm" target="_blank">http://darqsmoke.8m.net/Necromancers.htm</a></P><P>********Note************</P><P>These are merely suggestions.  I do not expect that all of them will be changed, or even if half them will be changed.  Some things may be to powerful, some may be underpowered.  This is just a compilation of all the posts on the EQ Necro forum about proposed changes to the Necromancer class.  Thanks</P><P> </P><P>            At level 46, a Necromancer’s role changes.  In the past, they could play solo and group efficiently.  Post 46 though, the focus changes from outdoor to indoor or planar zones.  This can be made evident in the obvious popularity of zones like Temple of Veeshan, Kanor’s Castle, Chardok, Velks Labyrinth, Sebilis, the Hole, and the Planes.  High level equipment, at least the good stuff, are located on monsters in dungeons, so that is where players go.  Necromancers need to be changed in order to be able to adapt to the new playing style.  </P><P> </P><P> </P><P>Check these locations for more descriptive reasons behind the proposed changes:<BR>Necro Site 1<BR>Necro Site 2         <BR>Necro Site 3<BR>Necro Site 4</P><P> <BR>Proposed Changes :</P><P>Pets (w/ focus):</P><P>Level 49 pet (unchanged) -- Invoke Death<BR>Hit Points: 2400<BR>Max Hit: 57<BR>Additional Abilities: Bash/Kick 25, Life Drain (40)<BR> <BR>Level 53 pet -- Minion of Shadows<BR>Hit Points: 2400<BR>Max Hit: 59<BR>Additional Abilities: Backstab 165, Life Drain (50)</P><P>Level 56 pet -- Servant of Bones<BR>Hit Points: 2900<BR>Max Hit: 61<BR>Additional Abilities: Flying Kick 73, Life Drain (60)</P><P>Level 59 pet -- Emissary of Thule (spectre)<BR>Hit Points: 3500<BR>Max Hit: 61<BR>Additional Abilities: Bash/Stun: 40, Life Drain (80), Spectre Stun (25), Fear Immunity<BR>Additional Costs: Peridot (1); no bone chips (its a spectre!)<BR> <BR>Also please fix the graphic and the lifetap of our pets</P><P>Second Option for pets<BR> <BR>Pet buff spells</P><P>Painful death (53) – Works only on lvl 49 Pet.  Increases pet hitpoints to 2600. Adds a 12 point damage shield (ie banshee aura).  Increases pet lifetap power by 10 percent.  Indoor only (and raid only zones)</P><P>Reapers Curse (56) – Works only on the lvl 49 Pet.  Increases pet hitpoints to 3000.  Adds a 25 point Damage shield.  (ie Screaming Banshee suggested spell).  Increases pet lifetap power by 20 percent.  Increases pets immunity to fear.  Indoor and raid only zones.</P><P>Gift of Thule (60) – Works only on the lvl 59 pet.  Increases pet hitpoints to 3500.  Adds a 32 point Damage Shield.  Increases pet spells efficiency by 20 percent.  Increase Max hit to 61.   Indoor and raid only zones.<BR> </P><P>Pet Commands:</P><P>/pet hold – this is designed to counter act poor pathing and pet bugs.  This should be in from level 1, and not an alternate advancement skill.<BR> <BR>/pet heel – basically the same effect as above.  Allows the casters to set a distance in which the pet can’t go out of.  This is designed to make moving in a dungeon with a pet safer.  Just in case pet strays into an area of bad pathing, this will prevent him from getting more that a certain distance from the caster.  This could be an alternate advancement skill, but I think it should be in from level one also.</P><P>Spell Changes:</P><P>First off, move all spells to locations reachable, with one group, by a caster of that level.  Also make them common drop.  Also make sure that when resistance was changed some time ago, that it effected not only direct damage spells but also damage over time spells.  </P><P>Lvl 54 Succussion of Shadows:<BR>Mana: 375<BR>Effect: Decrease mob AC by 60 and gives 60AC to EACH person in group<BR>Duration: 5mins</P><P>Lvl 56 Crippling Claudication:<BR>Mana: 375<BR>Effect: Decrease mob ATK by 50 and give 50 ATK to EACH person in group.<BR>Duration: 5mins</P><P>Lvl 58 Mind Wrack:<BR>Mana: 300<BR>Effect: Gives everyone in group a 12 mana per tick regen for 2 mins <BR>Duration: 2 mins<BR>Recast Time: instant</P><P>Note:  Stacks with everything except clarity line.  </P><P>(This is basically a mana buff.  Its 1 mana better than clarity 2 but it costs 5135 more mana.  I personally like to see 15 mana per tick, Clarity 2 would still be much more efficient )</P><P>2nd suggestion</P><P>Lvl 58 Mink Wrack (DD style):<BR>Mana: 1200<BR>Effect:  splits 1200 mana to all CASTERS in the group or 200 to everyone if that isn’t possible. <BR>Recast time: 2 mins<BR> <BR>Lvl 60 Zevfeer's Theft of Vitae:<BR>Mana: 600<BR>Effect: Drains mob's HP by 1980, and gives 330hp to EACH person in group, over 45 seconds.<BR>Recast time: 2mins</P><P>Note on all of these:  Make the recast times on all of these spells instant, but place an effect, with duration in line with the spells duration, on the party members so the spell can not be chain cast.  Also make this effect not cancel out mez, like DoTs do.  <BR> <BR>Quivering Veil of Xarn – Remove the illusion, and the night time only effect.  If it hasn’t been already</P><P>Trucidation– Remove the need for an essence emerald.  Replace it with another regent or none at all.  </P><P>Infussion – Remove the need for an essence emerald.  Change to a mana DoT.  Decrease the mana gained by half.  Make it require a peridot.</P><P>Levant – Remove the nighttime only stipulation.</P><P>Arch Lich – Add ultravision and fear immunity.</P><P>Personal Summon Corpse – make sure this spell is dropping. </P><P>Vexing Mordania – Add 500 hps to the amount drained and 500 hps to the amount gained, Reduce Duration to 40 seconds</P><P><BR>Proposed new spell ideas:</P><P>Buffs</P><P>Screaming Banshee (L49)  - Damage shield (25)<BR>Banshee possession(L44)  - Targeted version of Banshee Aura (12)<BR>Screaming Banshee Possession (54)  - Target version of Screaming Banshee (25)<BR>Reaper’s Aura(L40) – Grim Aura Upgrade – Increases Attack of Target by 25.<BR>Dead Man Walking (44) – Dead man floating, without the floating.  No zone restriction<BR>Group Dead Man Walking(49) – Group version of Dead Man Walking.</P><P>Debuffs, mez and misc</P><P>Shadow Storm(L49) - Takes 75 AC from target and gives to self<BR>Paralyzing Fear (L54) – AoE effect Stun/Mem (Screaming Terror upgrade) blur spell, with a lower resist.  Duration 20 seconds  <BR>Death Peace (51) – Same as the Shadow Knight Version.  We are the parent class.  <BR>Engulfing Shadows (59) – Two ideas for this spell.  Either a group version of Levant or a spell that changed it to night in the zone. <BR>Shackle of Soul (55) – Undead only slow. max 65 percent</P><P> </P><P>DD and DoTs</P><P>Infection (L58)  - Upgrade to Envenomed Bolt.  Does 1500 damage in 30 seconds<BR>Decay (55) - Disease based Deflux similar to the disease based Touch of Night at level 60.<BR>Tear of Cazic Thule (54) – Upgrade to Torbids Acid Blast (max 700dd)<BR>Chilling grip (L56) – Upgrade to Chilling Embrace.  1200 dmg over 45 seconds.  <BR>Shock of Senses: (L60) -  Mind Wrack upgrade.  Cost 2000 mana.  Gives 1000 mana to every member of the group.  Recast time: 10 minutes</P><P> </P><P>Spell Lines:</P><P>Spell Line: Resist Fear (16-54) – Increase target’s resistance to fear<BR>Spell Line: Degenerate (16-54) – Decreases the targets regeneration rate.<BR>Spell Line:  Confusion (16-54) – Decreases the amount in which the target regains mana. (would be a good mage line too)</P><P><BR>Epic</P><P>There are many ideas on this.  To save man power at Verant, I would suggest a contest.  Necromancers submit pictures to Verant with effect.  Design team picks 10 best ideas.  The player base votes on these ideas, with the option of not choosing any.  The winner gets the newest version of the epic, and the necro epic is changed to his design.  </P><P><BR>Faction<BR> <BR>A way to increase our faction with Venril Sathir</P><P><BR>Possible Idea for Alternate Advancement</P><P>Infected – Lvl 59 required. 9 training points.  Increases damage output of all poison and disease based dots by 50 percent.  </P><P><BR>Smaaug Darqsmoke<BR>Iksar Necromancer<BR>Brell Serilis</font></td>
